I've always wanted to go to a CES event and walk amongst all the exhibitors to see the newest concepts and designs presented by so many companies. This year. CES was virtual (thanks COVID-19). While I didn't attend, I was excited by so many applications of the technologies in the healthcare and wellness + accessibility space. In this post, I'm going to talk about some of the technologies I was excited about and their potential applications.

